20recession%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20according%20to%20Adam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E1.%20Labor%20market%20is%20weakening%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20labor%20market's%20strength%20is%20finally%20starting%20to%20wane.%20First%2C%20the%20pace%20of%20job%20growth%20has%20slowed%20considerably%2C%20with%20the%20three-month%20moving%20average%20falling%20to%20its%20lowest%20level%20since%202019.%20Second%2C%20job%20openings%20are%20starting%20to%20fade%2C%20down%20over%20three%20million%20from%20the%20recent%20peak.%20Third%2C%20consumer%20expectations%20of%20the%20labor%20market%20are%20moderating%2C%20with%20the%20%25%20of%20consumers%20stating%20that%20jobs%20are%20'hard%20to%20get'%20climbing%20to%20its%20highest%20level%20since%20April%202021%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdam%20also%20highlighted%20that%20a%20recent%20report%20suggested%20that%20seasonal%20hiring%20at%20retailers%20during%20the%20upcoming%20holidays%20could%20be%20the%20weakest%20since%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E2.%20Headwinds%20for%20the%20consumer%20are%20building%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20resilience%20of%20consumer%20spending%20is%20likely%20to%20come%20to%20a%20halt%20as%20the%20labor%20market%20softens%2C%20pandemic-era%20excess%20savings%20are%20fully%20depleted%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-will-government-shutdown-affect-student-loan-payment-resumption-debt-2023-9%5C%22%3Estudent%20loan%20payments%20resume%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20three%20years%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20according%20to%20the%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20student%20loan%20payments%20set%20to%20resume%20on%20October%201%20and%20gas%20prices%20rising%20as%20oil%20prices%20move%20higher%2C%20consumers%20should%20have%20less%20discretionary%20income%20to%20spend%20going%20forward.%20This%20has%20already%20started%20to%20spill%20over%20into%20weaker%20travel%20demand%2C%26quot%3B%20Adam%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E3.%20High%20borrowing%20rates%20reach%20a%20tipping%20point%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20mortgage%2C%20auto%20and%20credit%20card%20rates%20at%20multi-year%20highs%2C%20demand%20for%20loans%20from%20households%20has%20fallen%20dramatically.%20Banks%20are%20not%20only%20less%20willing%20to%20lend%3B%20the%20cost%20of%20borrowing%20has%20become%20prohibitive.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20average%20monthly%20payment%20on%20mortgages%20and%20auto%20loans%20is%20up%20over%2070%25%20since%202019!%20And%20with%20mortgage%20rates%20now%20well%20above%207.0%25%20and%20house%20prices%20still%20elevated%20due%20to%20the%20inventory%20shortages%2C%20affordability%20is%20becoming%20a%20serious%20dilemma%2C%26quot%3B%20Adam%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20housing%20market%20has%20a%20multiplier%20effect%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20as%20the%20purchase%20of%20a%20house%20typically%20includes%20big%20spending%20on%20appliances%2C%20home%20decor%2C%20and%20home%20improvements%2C%20among%20other%20categories.%20But%20with%20prospective%20buyers%20delaying%20their%20home%20purchase%20and%20existing%20homeowners%20%26quot%3Bfrozen%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20homes%20because%20of%20the%20current%20mortgage%20rate%20dynamic%2C%20that%20multiplier%20spending%20effect%20%26quot%3Bis%20likely%20to%20dry%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E4.%20Chances%20of%20a%20government%20shutdown%20are%20rising%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20worries%20us%20this%20time%20around%20is%20the%20timing.%20In%20isolation%2C%20past%20government%20shutdowns%20have%20not%20been%20a%20major%20market%20moving%20event.%20However%2C%20if%20there%20is%20a%20government%20shutdown%2C%20at%20a%20time%20when%20growth%20headwinds%20are%20building%20and%20strike%20activity%20(e.g.%2C%20United%20Auto%20Workers)%20is%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20the%20collective%20impact%20of%20all%20these%20forces%20could%20be%20more%20potent%20than%20what%20is%20expected%2C%26quot%3B%20Adam%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessi