C%C2%A02022%2C%C2%A0citing%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20as%20his%20reason%20for%20wanting%20to%20leave%20the%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20luxury%20of%20the%20Olivye%20palace%20compound%2C%20compared%20with%20ordinary%20Russian%20lives%2C%20also%20disgusted%20Brizhaty%2C%20he%20now%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20could%20never%20understand%20why%20Russia%2C%20such%20a%20rich%20country%2C%20has%20to%20suffer%20%E2%80%94%20why%20Russians%20cannot%20live%20well%2C%20and%20only%20the%20government%20can%20live%20so%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELooking%20out%20for%20%26quot%3BNumber%20One%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20documents%20seen%20by%20Insider%2C%20Brizhaty%2C%20a%20dog%20handler%2C%20joined%20the%20FSO%20in%202021.%20He%20told%20Insider%20he%20was%20stationed%20at%20the%20palace%20of%20Olivye%2C%20a%20Soviet-era%20state-owned%20complex%20that%20has%20been%20in%20Putin's%20use%20since%20the%202014%20annexation%20of%20Crimea.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FSO%20has%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2022%2F03%2F30%2Fcan-putin-be-overthrown-russias-leader-has-sought-to-prevent-a-coup.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimated%2050%2C000%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20protecting%20Putin%20and%20his%20senior%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrizhaty's%20job%20was%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-doesnt-even-trust-own-bodyguards-gives-fake-plans-defector-2023-9%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%3Ehelp%20make%20security%20arrangements%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20Putin's%20arrival%20at%20the%20palace%20or%20around%20Crimea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Putin%20%E2%80%94%20known%20internally%20as%20%26quot%3BNumber%20One%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20was%20due%20to%20visit%20a%20school%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%26quot%3Bour%20service%20would%20arrive%20nine%20hours%20prior%20to%20the%20visit%20and%20check%20the%20entire%20territory%20thoroughly%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20arrival%20of%20%26quot%3BNumber%20One%26quot%3B%20in%20Crimea%20demonstrated%20how%20little%20Putin%20trusted%20his%20own%20security%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20handled%20in%20two%20different%20ways%2C%20with%20most%20of%20Putin's%20own%20officers%20unaware%20of%20the%20real%20route.%20%26quot%3BNinety%20percent%20of%20the%20people%20do%20not%20know%20how%20he%20would%20arrive%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Brizhaty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20could%20either%20be%20a%20huge%20fanfare%2C%20with%20every%20airport%20on%20alert%20with%20a%20flurry%20of%20cars%2C%20helicopters%2C%20and%20ranks%20of%20guards%2C%20with%20a%20cortege%20moving%20between%20airports%20pretending%20that%20Putin%20was%20in%20one%20of%20the%20cars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOr%2C%20Brizhaty%20said%2C%20there%20would%20be%20total%20silence.%20%26quot%3BSuddenly%20the%20police%20gets%20word%20that%20Putin%20is%20somewhere%20in%20Crimea%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20and%20barely%20anybody%20would%20know%20how.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20lavish%20%26quot%3Blittle%20town%26quot%3B%20behind%2010-foot%20walls%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.proekt.media%2Freport%2Fdacha-krym%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202019%20investigation%20by%20the%20independent%20Russian%20outlet%20Proekt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20palace%20at%20Olivye%20is%20a%20vast%20complex%20and%20includes%20a%20competition-standard%20ice%20hockey%20rink%2C%20swimming%20pools%2C%20saunas%2C%20a%2060-bed%20staff%20dormitory%20with%20marble%20walls%20and%20a%20marble%20elevator%2C%20and%20a%20winter%20garden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESatellite%20images%20of%20the%20site%20also%20appear%20to%20show%20woodlands%2C%20beaches%2C%20a%20small%20port%2C%20and%20a%20helipad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20fantasy%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-paranoid-armed-divers-assassins-russia-crimea-2023-9%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%3EBrizhaty%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Telegraph's%20translation%20of%20an%20interview%20he%20gave%20independent%20Russian%20outlet%20TV%20Rain.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20fitness%20halls%2C%20fountains%2C%20beautiful%20parks%2C%20tea%20houses%2C%20barbecue%20zones%20and%20beaches.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArmed%20divers%20also%20scour%20the%20beach%20for%20assassins%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-paranoid-armed-divers-assassins-russia-crimea-2023-9%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%3Ehe%20told%20TV%20Rain.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20key%20aspect%20of%20the%20compound%20was%20that%20no%20matter%20their%20actual%20job%2C%20every%20single%20member%20of%20staff%20there%20was%20a%20security%20officer%2C%20Brizhaty%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20who%20works%20there%2C%20%5Beven%5D%20a%20person%20who%20is%20cutting%20the%20grass%20or%20washing%20the%20linen%2C%20works%20for%20the%20FSO%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Brizhaty%20had%20long%20quietly%20supported%20the%20views%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-life-career-of-putin-critic-alexei-navalny-2023-9%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%3Edissident%20Russian%20campaigner%20Alexei%20Navalny%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20says%20that%20as%20far%20as%20he%20knew%2C%20everybody%20else%20there%20was%20loyal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20people%20truly%20believe%20that%20they%20are%20doing%20an%20important%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20notice%20the%20luxury%2C%20or%20they%20believe%20that%20the%20president%20has%20a%20right%20to%20have%20this%20luxury.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrizhaty%20said%20he%20earned%2068%2C000%20rubles%20(about%20%24700)%20a%20month%2C%20but%20said%20a%20sharp-elbowed%20working%20culture%20kept%20him%20on%20his%20toes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20co-workers%20were%20more%20agreeable%2C%20many%20appeared%20to%20take%20a%20leaf%20out%20of%20Putin's%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20people%20there%20who%20are%20like%20him.%20It's%20hard%20to%20explain%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20trying%20to%20find%20faults%20with%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20watch%20everything%20you%20are%20saying%20in%20front%20of%20them%2C%20because%20every%20word%20may%20be%20used%20against%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20thing%20is%2C%20this%20is%20the%20kind%20of%20service%20where%20nothing%20happens%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20only%20way%20to%20make%20a%20career%20and%20to%20promote%20yourself%20is%20to%20tell%20on%20others.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EForced%20to%20protect%20a%20warmonger%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20culture%20was%20a%20particular%20problem%20for%20Brizhaty%20when%20Putin's%20tanks%20rolled%20across%20Ukraine's%20borders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrizhaty%2C%20who%20was%20under%20no%20illusions%20that%20it%20was%20a%20full-scale%20invasion%20%E2%80%93%20despite%20everyone%20around%20him%20calling%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bspecial%20military%20operation%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20offered%20his%20resignation%20the%20same%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20torn%20up%20and%20thrown%20in%20the%20trash%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20told%20that%20my%20anti-war%20position%20may%20result%20in%20an%20arrest%2C%20and%20I%20may%20end%20up%20in%20prison%20for%20about%20eight%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20under%20such%20pressure%20after%20that%20that%20even%20the%20psychologist%20he%20reached%20out%20to%20passed%20information%20from%20their%20private%20sessions%20straight%20back%20to%20his%20superiors%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20Brizhaty%20found%20a%20loophole%20that%20would%20allow%20him%20to%20leave%3A%20his%20wife%20found%20a%20job%20abroad%20and%20he%20was%20able%20to%20accompany%20her%20to%20Ecuador.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20weeks%20before%20that%20he%20was%20under%20immense%20pressure%20to%20renounce%20his%20views%2C%20he%20said%2C%20which%20forced%20him%20to%20stay%20quiet%20while%20forming%20a%20secret%20plan%20to%20get%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20in%20exile%2C%20Brizhaty%20says%20that%20the%2010-foot-high%20fence%20that%20surrounds%20the%20palace%20at%20Olivye%20is%20a%20potent%20symbol%20of%20the%20divide%20between%20Putin%20and%20the%20Russian%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20works%20for%20the%20people%2C%20and%20he%20should%20work%20in%20people's%20interests%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20should%20not%20protect%20himself%20against%20his%20own%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-luxury-palace-like-toxic-little-town-said-defector-guard-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695642633000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65115282e2c0220019ef3d61%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-luxury-palace-like-toxic-little-town-said-defector-guard-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Vitaly%20Brizhaty%2C%20a%20dissident%20former%20FSO%20officer%2C%20worked%20to%20protect%20Putin%20at%20his%20Crimea%20palace%2C%20where%20lackeys%20vied%20for%20power%20behind%2010-foot-high%20walls.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Mia%20Jankowicz)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-luxury-palace-like-toxic-little-town-said-defector-guard-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Golden%20Horse%20Film%20Project%20Market%20Sets%20Bumper%2064-Title%20Edition%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695642398000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2014%2F11