or-india-house-panel%2Farticle67341734.ece%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20the%20panel%20said%20that%20while%20MEME%20has%20been%20successfully%20implemented%20in%20the%20West%2C%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20to%20execute%20in%20India.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20institutions%20allow%20MEME%2C%20it%20would%20be%20very%20difficult%20for%20the%20institutions%20to%20predict%20how%20many%20students%20would%20exit%20and%20how%20many%20would%20join%20midway.%20Since%20institutions%20would%20not%20know%20the%20in-%20and%20out-traffic%2C%20it%20will%20certainly%20disturb%20the%20pupil-teacher%20ratio%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20uneven%20geographical%20distribution%20of%20higher%20educational%20institutions%20would%20create%20hurdles%20in%20managing%20MEME%20in%20several%20areas%2C%20mostly%20countryside.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20institutions%20have%20not%20thought%20very%20clearly%20about%20this%20problem%20and%20how%20they%20will%20resolve%20it%20when%20it%20is%20at%20their%20doorstep%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fnational-education-policy-funding-implementation-centralisation%5C%22%3EThe%20National%20Education%20Policy%20Has%20a%20Grand%20Vision%20but%20Can%E2%80%99t%20See%20Its%20Own%20Feet%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20recognising%20that%20MEME%20would%20offer%20students%20greater%20flexibility%20and%20choice%20in%20their%20educational%20pathways%2C%20the%20panel%20asked%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Feducation%2Fnational-education-policy-2020-multiple-entry-multiple-exit-option-may-not-work-well-for-india-house-panel%2Farticle67341734.ece%5C%22%3Edevelop%20comprehensive%20guidelines%20and%20a%20well-defined%20framework%20for%20MEME%20options%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20specific%20eligibility%20criteria%2C%20credit%20transfer%20mechanisms%20and%20a%20clear%20road%20map%20for%20students%20pursuing%20different%20exit%20points.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAlso%2C%20implementation%20of%20a%20standardised%20Credit%20Accumulation%20and%20Transfer%20(CAT)%20system%20that%20allows%20students%20to%20earn%20and%20transfer%20credits%20seamlessly%20across%20institutions%20would%20facilitate%20smooth%20transitions%20between%20different%20levels%20of%20education%2C%20from%20certificate%20courses%20to%20doctoral%20programmes%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20panel%20also%20asked%20the%20Union%20education%20ministry%20to%20hold%20discussions%20with%20various%20educational%20institutions%20and%20their%20regulatory%20bodies%20to%20understand%20the%20problems%20in%20NEP%E2%80%99s%20implementation%20and%20what%20can%20be%20done%20to%20address%20these%20challenges.%20The%20committee%20has%20asked%20the%20ministry%20to%20apprise%20it%20of%20the%20findings%20after%20these%20consultations%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Feducation%2Fnational-education-policy-2020-multiple-entry-multiple-exit-option-may-not-work-well-for-india-house-panel%2Farticle67341734.ece%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20students%20and%20teachers%20raised%20apprehensions%20about%20the%20proposed%20exit%20and%20entry%20system.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20will%20reduce%20the%20value%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20degree%20and%20this%20is%20a%20way%20to%20produce%20cheap%20labour%20for%20the%20job%20market.%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20eyewash%20and%20we%20want%20the%20existing%20system%20to%20continue%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mayukh%20Biswas%2C%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20Students%20Federation%20of%20India%20(SFI)%20was%20quoted%20by%20the%20paper%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695629751000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24164751%2F1599px-Indian_Students_4616.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fmultiple-entry-exit-points-under-nep-unfit-for-indian-education-system-parliamentary-panel%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CIf%20institutions%20allow%20multiple%20exits%2C%20it%20would%20be%20very%20difficult%20for%20the%20institutions%20to%20predict%20how%20many%20students%20would%20exit%20and%20how%20many%20would%20join%20midway%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20panel%20said%20in%20its%20report.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fmultiple-entry-exit-points-under-nep-unfit-for-indian-education-system-parliamentary-panel%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20the%20DDA's%20Land%20Pooling%20Policy%20Has%20Led%20to%20Concerns%20Among%20Landowning%20Villagers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25134124%2F9125819359_cc40fa1841_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20its%20provisional%20notice%20on%20May%2019%2C%202022%2C%20for%20the%20formation%20of%20a%20consortium%20under%20the%20land%20pooling%20policy%20and%20regulations%2C%20the%20Deputy%20Director%20(Land%20Pooling)%20initiated%20the%20process%20for%20the%20Sector%202%20and%20Sector%203%20in%20Zone%20P-II%20and%20Sector%2010A%20in%20Zone%20N%20of%20Delhi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20eligibility%20criteria%20%E2%80%93%20of%20a%20minimum%20of%2070%25%20of%20the%20developable%20area%20in%20the%20sector%20needing%20to%20be%20pooled%20%E2%80%93%20was%20fulfilled.%20The%20Delhi%20Development%20Authority%20(DDA)%20then%20issued%20a%20provisional%20notice%20to%20the%20three%20sectors.%20The%20notice%20further%20stated%20that%20the%20consortium%20has%20to%20be%20formed%20within%2090%20days%20of%20the%20issue%20of%20this%20notice%20along%20with%20fulfilment%20of%20the%20condition%20that%2070%25%20of%20the%20land%20for%20each%20of%20the%20three%20sectors%20needs%20to%20be%20contiguous.%20This%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20been%20fulfilled%20yet.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20policy%20was%20notified%20on%20October%2024%2C%202018.%20As%20per%20the%20regulations%2C%20a%20consortium%20is%20defined%20as%20a%20registered%20association%20having%20rights%2C%20duties%20and%20obligations%20in%20accordance%20with%20law%2C%20constituting%20of%20multiple%20landowners%20or%20developer%20entities%20who%20have%20come%20together%20to%20pool%20the%20land%20as%20per%20policy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123347%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.33.37-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22614%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123347%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.33.37-PM.png%20934w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123347%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.33.37-PM-239x300.png%20239w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123347%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.33.37-PM-817x1024.png%20817w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674713%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22769%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EProvisional%20notice%20for%20formation%20of%20consortium%20issued%20by%20DDA.%20Source%3A%20DDA%2C%20Land%20Pooling%20Website%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETill%20October%2031%2C%202022%2C%20as%20per%20the%20data%20released%20by%20the%20DDA%2C%2087.1%25%2C%2081.5%25%20and%2098.4%25%20of%20land%20is%20tentatively%20pooled%20in%20Section%202%20and%20Section%203%20in%20Zone%20P-II%2C%20and%20Section%2010%20A%20in%20Zone%20N.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20compared%20across%20sectors%20in%20four%20land%20pooling%20zones%20in%20Delhi%2C%20these%20are%20very%20high%20percentages%20of%20land%20pooled%20under%20the%20policy.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20notice%20also%20advocated%20for%20encouragement%20of%20non-participating%20landowners%20in%20these%20sectors%20to%20participate.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123651%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.36.43-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123651%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.36.43-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123651%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.36.43-PM-300x212.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123651%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.36.43-PM-1024x723.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674738%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22847%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELand%20pooled%20map%20for%20Sector-2%20Zone%20P-II.%20The%20area%20statement%20shows%20that%20though%20the%20sector%20has%20been%20able%20to%20pool%C2%A0%2087.8%25%20of%20land%2C%20only%2065.79%25%20of%20the%20total%20pooled%20land%20is%20contiguous.%20Source%3A%20DDA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20provisional%20notice%20issued%20to%20these%20three%20sectors%20was%20hailed%20as%20one%20of%20the%20big%20steps%20under%20the%20much-delayed%20land%20pooling%20exercise.%20Stakeholders%20have%20largely%20been%20advocating%20for%20the%20speedy%20implementation%20of%20the%20policy.%20Demarcating%20the%20sector%20boundary%20along%20with%20proposed%20roads%20and%20location%20of%20villages%2C%20DDA%20had%20installed%20signages%20in%20the%20proposed%20sectors.%20This%20further%20raised%20hope%20among%20the%20stakeholders.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123936%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.39.26-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123936%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.39.26-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123936%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.39.26-PM-300x221.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123936%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.39.26-PM-1024x755.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674771%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22885%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EProposed%20Sector%202%20Zone%20P-II%20map%20installed%20on%20a%20display%20board%20in%20the%20Tigipur%20village.%C2%A0Photo%3A%20Ritesh%20Rana%2C%20Bakhtawarpur%20village%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20there%20have%20been%20discussions%20going%20on%20to%20amend%20the%20Delhi%20Development%20Act%2C%201957%2C%20to%20make%20land%20pooling%20mandatory%20for%20those%20landowners%20who%20have%20not%20expressed%20willingness%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20policy%20if%20minimum%2070%25%20criteria%20is%20achieved.%20These%20amendments%20were%20announced%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Affairs%20minister%2C%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Puri.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20amendments%20are%20in%20contravention%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98voluntary%20participation%20clause%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20policy%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20non-democratic%20and%20participatory%20principles%20of%20any%20land%20policy.%20After%20issuing%20conditional%20notices%2C%20the%20DDA%20held%20public%20meetings%20in%20the%20month%20of%20July%202022%20in%20the%20villages%20of%20Sector%202%20and%20Sector%203%20on%20the%20land%20pooling%20policy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20DDA%20till%20date%20has%20provided%20four%20extension%20notices%20to%20the%20all%20the%20three%20sectors%20to%20form%20the%20consortium.%20The%2090-day%20deadline%20is%20long%20gone.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20latest%20notice%20issued%20by%20DDA%20mentioned%20the%20extension%20up%20to%20March%2031%2C%202023%2C%20for%20three%20sectors.%20However%2C%20even%20after%20five%20months%20of%20the%20deadline%2C%20no%20consortium%20has%20been%20formed%20in%20these%20three%20sectors.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20DDA%20has%20issued%20provisional%20notices%20to%2010%20other%C2%A0%20sectors%20across%20different%20zones.%20It%20has%20also%20conveyed%20through%20a%20public%20notice%20that%20in%20Sector%208B%20in%C2%A0%20Zone%20P-II%2C%20a%20consortium%20was%20registered%20on%20February%2027%2C%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20unclear%20as%20to%20why%20this%20delay%20is%20taking%20place%20in%20forming%20the%20consortiums.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25130757%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-1.07.41-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221104%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25130757%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-1.07.41-PM.png%201104w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25130757%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-1.07.41-PM-276x300.png%20276w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25130757%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-1.07.41-PM-942x1024.png%20942w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-675030%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENotice%20regarding%20extension%20of%20time%20period%20to%20form%20consortium%20issued%20by%20DDA.%20Source%3A%20DDA%2C%20Land%20Pooling%C2%A0website%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20significant%20challenges%20in%20the%20formation%20of%20consortium%20is%20the%20small%20parcels%20of%20land%20is%20multiplicity%20of%20ownership.%20For%20instance%2C%20details%20of%20registered%20applicants%20who%20have%20shown%20willingness%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20policy%20from%20Sector%202%20Zone%20P-II%20points%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20majority%20of%20the%20landowners%20own%20land%20less%20than%20one%20hectare.%20With%20varied%20interests%20and%20each%20landowner%20trying%20to%20reap%20maximum%20benefits%20from%20the%20land%20pooling%20policy%2C%20there%20has%20been%20significant%20mistrust%20among%20landowners%20too.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESanjay%20Thakran%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20broker%20from%20Sector%2010A%20Zone%20N%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMaking%20the%20consortium%20is%20the%20biggest%20issue.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20are%20saying%20that%20one%20person%20will%20represent%20us%20and%20submit%20papers%20to%20the%20DDA.%20Now%2C%20if%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20someone%2C%20why%20would%20I%20give%20them%20charge%20of%20my%20land%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fthe-missing-villagers-of-the-ddas-green-development-policy%5C%22%3EThe%20Missing%20Villagers%20of%20the%20DDA%E2%80%99s%20Green%20Development%20Policy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20DDA%20says%20to%20first%20form%20a%20group%20of%20100-150%20people%20and%20then%20submit%20one%E2%80%99s%20land%20to%20some%20builder.%20Now%20a%20farmer%E2%80%99s%20concern%20is%20what%20will%20he%20do%20if%20the%20builder%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20take%20any%20action.%20DDA%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20give%20any%20money%20to%20the%20landowners.%20Our%20say%20is%20that%20either%20you%20scrap%20this%20consortium%20formation%20clause%20or%20else%20bring%20people%20together%20on%20this.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20announcement%20by%20DDA%20for%20the%20provisional%20notice%20was%20also%20seen%20as%20a%20major%20step%20that%20might%20impact%20the%20land%20prices%20in%20the%20villages.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMultiple%20interactions%20with%20landowners%20in%20land%20pooling%20villages%20have%20pointed%20to%20the%20steep%20rise%20and%20decline%20in%20land%20prices%20due%20to%20sudden%C2%A0%20announcements%20by%20authorities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20landowner%20from%20Sector%202%20Zone%20P-II%2C%20on%20the%20consortium%20notice%20by%20DDA%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202010-2011%20when%20discussions%20around%20the%20policy%20were%20happening%2C%20the%20rate%20was%20Rs%204-4.5%20crore%20per%20acre%20of%20land.%20Now%20it%20has%20gone%20down%20to%20Rs%201%20crore%20per%20acre.When%20the%20consortium%20notice%20came%2C%20the%20land%20prices%20should%20have%20increased%20to%20Rs%2010%20crore%20per%20acre%20and%20builders%20should%20have%20come%20in%20their%20cars%20inside%20the%20village%20with%C2%A0%20cash%20to%20purchase%20the%20land%20but%20there%20is%20no%20life%20in%20the%20policy.%20Why%20would%20investors%20come%20and%C2%A0%20invest%3F%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERTI%20correspondence%20with%20DDA%20and%20MoHUA%20has%20revealed%20that%20this%20policy%20has%20been%20reviewed%20and%20discussed%20in%20the%20PMO.%20But%20till%20date%20nothing%20has%20been%20finalised.%20The%20reply%20received%20two%20months%20ago%20stated%20that%20the%20matter%20is%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cexamination%20stage%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20the%20DDA%20has%20been%20historically%20blamed%20for%20the%20lack%20of%20trust%20among%20landowning%20villagers%2C%20with%20private%20players%20entering%20the%20policy%2C%20the%20landowners%20need%20an%20informed%20decision-making%20platform%20to%20come%20together.%20This%20is%20something%20that%20will%20not%20come%20about%20in%20the%20course%20of%20one%20or%20two%20meetings.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EParas%20Tyagi%20is%20president%20of%20Centre%20for%20Youth%20Culture%20Law%20and%20Environment%20(CYCLE)%2C%20a%20Delhi%20based%20non-profit%20organisation.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695629672000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25134124%2F9125819359_cc40fa1841_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fdelhi-land-pooling-policy-dda%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20DDA%20has%20been%20historically%20blamed%20for%20the%20lack%20of%20trust%20among%20Delhi's%20landowning%20villagers.%20One%20of%20its%20newer%20land%20pooling%20policy%20clauses%20deepens%20these%20divides.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fdelhi-land-pooling-policy-dda%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Celebs%20at%20CM%20Shinde's%20Ganpati%20Darshan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695629548000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103926779%2Cimgsize-75362.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Fshah-rukh-khan-to-salman-khan-bollywood-celebs-at-cm-shindes-ganpati-darshan%2Fphotostory%2F103926779.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20sr