ws-films-youll-have-to-wait-for%2Fa-66227440%5C%22%3Eit%E2%80%99s%20far%20from%20business%20as%20usual%20in%20Hollywood%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20actors%E2%80%99%20strike%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETalks%20between%20the%20studios%20and%20the%20striking%20actors%20have%20not%20yet%20resumed%2C%20so%20crew%20members%20left%20out%20of%20work%20by%20the%20walkout%20will%20remain%20unemployed%20for%20the%20time%20being.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20on%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftop-stories%2Fs-9097%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flogs1279.xiti.com%2Fhit.xiti%3Fs%3D531599%26s2%3D2%26p%3Dthewire.in%3A%3AVolltexte%3A%3Athewire.in_Volltexte_JS%26di%3D%26an%3D%26ac%3D%26x1%3D1%26x2%3D2%26x5%3Dthewire.in_Volltexte_JS%26x6%3D1%26x8%3Den-VAS-Volltexte-JavaScript-thewire.in-dwde%26x10%3Dthewire.in%3A%3AVolltexte%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695628847000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13155533%2FF02TdGIaYAAm33K.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fhollywood-writers-reach-tentative-deal-with-studios%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Striking%20writers%20will%20go%20back%20to%20work%20if%20the%20deal%20is%20approved%20by%20union%20members.%20Actors%20are%20still%20on%20strike%20over%20compensation%2C%20residual%20payments%20and%20AI%20protection%2C%20among%20other%20issues.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fhollywood-writers-reach-tentative-deal-with-studios%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20Number%20of%20Salaried%20Workers%20Rise%20in%20India%2C%20So%20Does%20Inequality%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F13160830%2FRajasthan-NREGA-workers.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20the%20growth%20of%20the%20economy%20since%20the%201980%E2%80%99s%20has%20pulled%20millions%20of%20workers%20out%20of%20agriculture%20and%20led%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20regular%20wage%20workers%2C%20this%20has%20not%20benefited%20everyone%20equally%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2Fstate-of-working-india%2Fswi-2023%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efinds%20a%20report%20by%20Azim%20Premji%20University.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESC%2FST%20communities%20and%20religious%20minorities%20underrepresented%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98State%20of%20Working%20India%202023%3A%20Social%20Identities%20and%20Labour%20Market%20Outcomes%E2%80%99%20finds%20that%20while%20growth%20created%20regular%20wage%20jobs%20for%20all%20castes%2C%20the%20rates%20differed%20significantly.%20There%20has%20been%20a%20rise%20in%20SC%20regular%20wage%20workers%2C%20with%20around%2022%25%20of%20SC%20workers%20being%20regular%20wage%20as%20compared%20to%2032%25%20of%20others%2C%20but%2040%25%20of%20SC%20workers%20were%20in%20casual%20employment%20as%20compared%20to%20only%2013%25%20for%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUpward%20mobility%20has%20increased%20and%20caste%20based%20segregation%20has%20decreased%2C%20and%20yet%20entrepreneurs%20belonging%20to%20SC%20and%20ST%20communities%20are%20still%20rare.%20SC%20and%20ST%20owners%20are%20underrepresented%20compared%20to%20their%20percentage%20of%20the%20total%20workforce%2C%20even%20in%20the%20smallest%20firms%2C%20while%20the%20overrepresentation%20of%20upper%20castes%20rises%20with%20the%20size%20of%20the%20firm.%20SC%2FST%20owners%20are%20more%20uncommon%20in%20larger%20firms.%20Owners%20of%20companies%20with%20more%20than%2020%20employees%20are%20hardly%20SC%20or%20ST.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20points%20out%20that%20while%20structures%20of%20employment%20vary%20more%20with%20reference%20to%20gender%20and%20caste%2C%20religious%20identities%20have%20played%20an%20important%20role%20as%20well.%20During%20the%20course%20of%20the%20four-decade%20period%20since%20the%2080s%2C%20after%20adjusting%20for%20education%2C%20household%20size%2C%20state%2C%20and%20other%20pertinent%20criteria%2C%20Muslims%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20hold%20regular%20wage%20jobs%20and%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20in%20own-account%20or%20casual%20pay%20work.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.minorityaffairs.gov.in%2FWriteReadData%2FRTF1984%2F7830578798.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Sachar%20Committee%20Report%20from%202006%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20made%20note%20of%20the%20chronic%20underrepresentation%20in%20regular%20wage%20labour%2C%20which%20remains%20a%20huge%20cause%20for%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fin-bundelkhand-dirty-work-is-done-by-the-lower-caste-only%5C%22%3EIn%20Bundelkhand%2C%20%E2%80%98Dirty%20Work%E2%80%99%20Is%20Done%20Only%20by%20the%20Lower%20Caste%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWomen%20face%20stereotypes%2C%20pay%20gaps%20and%20discrimination%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGender%20based%20earning%20disparities%20have%20also%20reduced%20since%202017%2C%20but%20remain%20prominent%20%E2%80%93%20women%20earn%2076%25%20of%20what%20men%20do%2C%20and%20SC%2FST%20women%20earn%2054%25%20of%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20women%E2%80%99s%20pay.%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Workforce%20Population%20Rate%20(WPR)%20has%20risen%2C%20due%20to%20a%20rise%20in%20self-employment%20caused%20by%20the%20pandemic%20and%20subsequent%20lockdown%2C%20female%20employment%20rates%20have%20increased%20since%202019.%2050%25%20of%20women%20were%20self-employed%20prior%20to%20COVID%2C%20which%20increased%20to%2060%25%20afterwards.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20self-employment%20earnings%20were%20just%2085%25%20of%20what%20they%20had%20been%20in%20the%20April-June%202019%20quarter%2C%20even%20two%20years%20after%20the%202020%20shutdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGender%20norms%20also%20play%20a%20heavy%20role%20in%20determining%20women%E2%80%99s%20employment%20status.%20The%20%E2%80%9Cmale%20breadwinner%E2%80%9D%20norm%2C%20in%20which%20husbands%20are%20regarded%20as%20the%20primary%20earners%20and%20females%20contribute%20to%20home%20money%20only%20when%20necessary%2C%20is%20a%20prevalent%20gender%20norm.%20The%20report%20finds%20that%20when%20the%20husband%E2%80%99s%20earnings%20are%20high%2C%20women%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20greater%20chance%20that%20wives%20will%20be%20employed%20when%20husbands%E2%80%99%20incomes%20climb%2C%20starting%20about%20Rs%2040%2C000%20per%20month.%20The%20report%20states%20that%20this%20trend%20might%20be%20the%20product%20of%20shifting%20social%20norms%20brought%20on%20by%20increased%20wealth%2C%20or%20it%20might%20be%20the%20effect%20of%20such%20husbands%20being%20paired%20with%20more%20educated%20wives%20who%20have%20preferences%20and%20possibilities%20to%20obtain%20better-paying%20jobs%2C%20pointing%20out%20how%20class%20and%20gender%20are%20barriers%20to%20obtaining%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPost-marriage%20life%20and%20rules%20remain%20a%20significant%20factor%20in%20determining%20women%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20work.%20Married%20women%20living%20in%20families%20where%20the%20mother-in-law%20is%20present%20but%20not%20employed%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20employed%20compared%20to%20households%20where%20there%20is%20no%20mother-in-law%20present%3B%20and%20daughters-in-laws%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20employed%20if%20the%20mother-in-law%20is%20also%20employed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20finds%20that%20women%20are%20employed%20in%20higher%20proportion%20in%20districts%20where%20domestic%20violence%20is%20more%20prevalent%2C%20which%20could%20be%20from%20the%20backlash%20effect%20%E2%80%93%20that%20because%20traditional%20gender%20roles%20are%20being%20challenged%2C%20working%20women%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20experience%20partner%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20rural%20areas%20of%20Karnataka%20and%20Rajasthan%2C%20women%E2%80%99s%20employment%20participation%20increased%20dramatically%20during%20the%20first%20five%20years%20of%20marriage.%20The%20majority%20of%20this%20employment%20was%20as%20self-employed%20farmers%20or%20as%20contributing%20family%20members.%20However%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20marriage%20or%20motherhood%20penalty%20indicates%20that%20this%20is%20work%20done%20out%20of%20compulsion%20in%20order%20to%20survive.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWomen%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20the%20workforce%20also%20varies%20across%20the%20different%20social%20groups%20within%20%E2%80%93%20in%202020%2C%20the%20WPR%20was%20lowest%20for%20Muslim%20women%2C%20at%20a%20despairing%2016.3%25.%20This%20points%20towards%20difficulty%20of%20mobility%20and%20opportunities%2C%20as%20well%20as%20possible%20discrimination%20by%20employers%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20gender%2C%20caste%20and%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EUnemployment%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20economic%20growth%20and%20employment%20creation%20are%20still%20only%20weakly%20related.%20The%20report%20indicates%20that%20policies%20favouring%20faster%20growth%20do%20not%20necessarily%20foster%20faster%20job%20creation.%20Between%202004%20and%202019%2C%20growth%20often%20led%20to%20respectable%20employment.%20The%20pandemic%2C%20which%20produced%20a%20bigger%20surge%20in%20distressed%20employment%2C%20interrupted%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20educational%20levels%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20is%20lower%20than%20it%20was%20before%20COVID.%20However%2C%20it%20continues%20to%20be%20above%2015%25%20for%20graduates%2C%20and%20more%20concerningly%2C%20it%20reaches%20a%20staggering%2042%25%20for%20graduates%20under%2025.%20Unemployment%20has%20fallen%2C%20but%20remains%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20points%20out%20the%20glaring%20discrimination%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20caste%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20religion%2C%20which%20prevent%20access%20to%20opportunities%20and%20play%20a%20role%20in%20low%20workforce%20participation%20rates%20and%20unemployment.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695628521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F13160830%2FRajasthan-NREGA-workers.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fas-number-of-salaried-workers-rise-in-india-so-does-inequality-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%98State%20of%20Working%20India%202023%3A%20Social%20Identities%20and%20Labour%20Market%20Outcomes%E2%80%99%20finds%20that%20while%20growth%20created%20regular%20wage%20jobs%20for%20all%20castes%2C%20the%20rates%20differed%20significantly.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fas-number-of-salaried-workers-rise-in-india-so-does-inequality-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UP%20school%20slapgate%3A%20SC%20wants%20senior%20IPS%20officer%20to%20probe%20case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695628355000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103926278%2Cimgsize-88396.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fstudent-slapping-case-supreme-court-asks-up-govt-to-appoint-senior-ips-officer-to-investigate-case%2Farticleshow%2F103926286.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Monday%20directed%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20government%20to%20appoint%20a%20senior%20IPS%20officer%20to%20investigate%20into%20a%20recent%20case%20of%20alleged%20slapping%20of%20a%20boy%20by%20his%20classmates%20at%20a%20private%20school%20in%20UP%E2%80%99s%20Muzaffarnagar.%20Terming%20the%20incident%20%26quot%3Bserious%26q